Good Morning,

To all WUSD staff and families,

Although we know that part of Windsor is still under an evacuation warning, given that we didn't have the dry lightning event that was projected to occur, schools will be open today.

Please share with your WUSD friends and families.

***********************************************************************
Buenos días,

A todo el personal y las familias de WUSD,

Aunque sabemos que parte de Windsor todavía está bajo una advertencia de evacuación, dado que no tuvimos el evento de rayo seco que se proyectaba, las escuelas estarán abiertas hoy.

Por favor, comparta con sus amigos y familias de WUSD.

post_text:
AUGUST 17TH CLASSES CANCELED FOR ALL WINDSOR UNIFIED SCHOOLS

Dear Windsor Unified School District Community:

As you may know, there are multiple power outages in the Windsor area. PG&E is working now, and currently estimates restoration by noon tomorrow, August, 17th. Therefore, there will be no classes Monday, August 17th, 2020. At this time we plan to resume classes Tuesday, August 18th. Please stay tuned for additional communication.

Sincerely,

Jeremy Decker

Superintendent

17 DE AGOSTO CLASES CANCELADAS PARA TODAS LAS ESCUELAS UNIFICADAS DE WINDSOR

Estimada comunidad del Distrito Escolar Unificado de Windsor:

Como sabrá, actualmente hay varios cortes de energía en el área de Windsor. PG&E está trabajando ahora y actualmente estima la restauración para el mediodía de mañana, 17 de agosto. Por lo tanto, no habrá clases el lunes 17 de agosto de 2020. En este momento planeamos iniciar las clases el martes 18 de agosto. Estén atentos para comunicaciones adicionales.

Sinceramente,

Jeremy Decker

Superintendente

Hi there,

Please see the Agenda for the Special Board Meeting on Monday, July 27th, 2020 at the following link.

https://go.boarddocs.com/ca/windsorusd/Board.nsf/Public

If you wish to give a public comment, please email me at jcox@wusd.org by 12:00pm on Monday, July 27th.

If you have any problems opening this agenda, you will also find it on the WUSD website by following these instructions:
Go to the main WUSD website, click on Menu, then District Leadership, then Board of Trustees, about half way down the page there is a link that says WUSD Board Packets, click on the link and it brings you to the posted BoardDocs meetings. We started using BoardDocs in January of this year. There is also a heading announcing the older board meetings, so everything from pre BoardDocs is listed there.

If you know of someone who would like to receive notification of the Board Meetings, please ask them to email me, I will add them to the distribution list.

If you have any questions please let me know.

Jenny Cox
Executive Assistant to the Superintendent
WUSD

Meal Box Pickup Tomorrow
Hello WUSD families: If you have pre-ordered School Lunch Meal Boxes for your students and children 18 yrs and younger, please remember to pick them up tomorrow from 11 am- 1pm at your designated school pickup location. Also, if you need additional food for your other family members, Redwood Empire Food Bank will also be distributing meal boxes in front of Windsor High School from 11 am-1pm. See you tomorrow! Hola Familias de WUSD, Si ha encargado el servicio de almuerzos escolares por adelantado, no se les olvide pasar a recoger su orden mañana de 11am - 1pm en la escuela que designó al ordenar. También, si necesita más recursos de comida para los adultos en su familia, la organización Redwood Empire Food Bank estará entregando cajas de comida enfrente de Windsor High School manana de 11am - 1pm. Nos vemos mañana!

post_text: Over the past couple of weeks, Windsor's IT team was gathering devices, testing functionality, sterilizing, and wrapping them for students. Yesterday and today, a team of Windsor Unified staff from every site joined the IT department and distributed devices to students. A very special THANK YOU to all who made the last couple of days possible.

Downtown Windsor, California
February 18 at 12:33 PM ·

Windsor is the place we call home. We’ve made it our mission to create a welcoming space for you to relax, stroll, drink, eat, talk, shop & celebrate.

We are a vibrant community of retailers & merchants, with one focus – to welcome you to Windsor and the experiences we have to offer. Stroll through our many. stores and find the perfect little something to treat yourself or gift to someone special.

Our Restaurants are the perfect spot to relax and enjoy delicious food and exquisite local wines for your next company lunch or family gathering.

Our Downtown offers a wide variety of spaces for you to leave your stresses behind and just be. Whether you are visiting us for a business meeting at one of our restaurants or a weekend away in Wine Country, come join us on the Town Green. #DowntownWindsor #ThePlaceToBe

2019-20 Calendar Updates

The List below are the changes to the 2019-20 calendar, necessitated by the days schools were closed for the fire.

All Scheduled Graduation & Promotion Ceremonies will remain the same.
February 7th will be a regular school day for students and staff. [previously a PD Day]
June 1st will be the last day of school for students.
June 1st will be a full day because we lost full days for fire days.
June 2nd will replace February 7th as a Professional Development Day

Town of Windsor, CA
November 20, 2019 at 12:26 PM ·

I Spy New Banners!

The Town installed new banners this week along Windsor Road. These banners were designed in partnership with students at Brooks Elementary School, Cali Calmecac Language Academy, the Town of Windsor Public Art Advisory Commission and the Town Council. In addition to the light poles along Windsor Road, 22 additional banners will be placed surrounding the Town Green in January 2020. These will replace the pennants which hang on the light poles from January to November. Artwork Credits:
Learning / aprendiendo – Selena Ramos
Parks / parques – Selena Ramos
Nature / naturaleza – Dalia Guzman
Community / comunidad – Victoria Plaza
Caring / afectuoso – Raquel Garcia
Well-being / bien estar – Dither Ochoa

For WUSD Staff Who Do NOT Have Direct Deposit

Lois Standring has been able to pick up the October 31st paychecks today from SCOE and will have them available for pick-up tomorrow. She will be at the District Office of Cotati-Rohnert Park School District between 10 a.m. and 12 p.m. on Thursday, October 31st. The office is located at 7165 Burton Ave in Rohnert Park. It is on the campus of a school and is in Building H towards the back of the campus. If you do not pick up the check tomorrow she will have the checks available at the Windsor District Office as soon as the evacuation order is lifted and power is restored. You can also request that your check be mailed to you. Please email lstandring@wusd.org with any questions or direction to mail your check.

post_text: WINDSOR: This is the most updated news from this morning's county press conference. We are all watching the winds today to make sure they don't blow the fire west again toward the 101 corridor, which includes us. This is why we all ask for your CONTINUED PATIENCE as we try to protect you! Also there is a CODE BLUE warning for the rest of the week for freezing temps at night. Please make sure you are bundled up and in a warm place! We will continue to keep you updated. Below is a photo of the National Guard who are protecting your homes and keeping people out for safety reasons. The Guard is at all entrances to Windsor and within the town as well. ❤️

Hola familias y empleados del Distrito Escolar Unificado de Windsor,

Debido a la continua incertidumbre en torno a las evacuaciones de los estudiantes y el personal, la amenaza de incendio, la disponibilidad de energía y las preocupaciones sobre la calidad del aire, las escuelas del Distrito Escolar Unificado de Windsor permanecerán cerradas por el resto de la semana (hasta el viernes 1 de noviembre).

Busque y escuche actualizaciones periódicas e información importante sobre nuestra escuela y distrito.

Su seguridad y bienestar (y los de su familia) son de suma importancia para nosotros. Esté seguro y tenga cuidado. Lo superaremos como comunidad.

post_text:
WUSD WILL REMAIN CLOSED THROUGH FRIDAY, NOVEMBER 1

Due to the continued uncertainty around evacuations of students and staff, fire threat, the availability of power, school conditions, and air quality concerns, Windsor Unified School District schools will remain closed for the rest of the week (through Friday, November 1).

Please look and listen for regular updates and important information about our school and district.

Your (and your family's) safety and well-being are of most important to us. Be safe and take care. We will get through this as a community.

Important Air Quality Reminder:

This link will connect you to information that was sent out earlier this year regarding the Air Quality Guidelines we follow:
https://www.wusd.org/article/139573?org=windsor-unified-school-district

We are receiving information indicating air quality in the "Unhealthy for Sensitive Groups" to "Unhealthy" ranges.

All prolonged outdoor activities (like recess and P.E.) will be moved indoors. Outdoor practices will be moved inside. Scheduled outdoor athletic games will follow CIF guidelines.

From the County of Sonoma
The Disaster Distress Helpline, 1-800-985-5990, is a hotline dedicated to providing immediate crisis counseling for people who are experiencing emotional distress related to any natural or human-caused disaster. You can also text 66746 to connect with a trained crisis counselor.

Town of Windsor, CA
October 24, 2019 at 2:18 AM ·

Large fire burning outside Geyserville, as of now there is no threat to Windsor. We are actively monitoring events and the Town of Windsor has activated our Emergency Operations Center (EOC) to be prepared in the event that conditions change.

Evacuation centers open for evacuees from Geyserville:
......Windsor High School - 8695 Windsor Rd. Windsor
......Healdsburg Community Center - 1557 Healdsburg Ave. Healdsburg
......Large animals - Santa Rosa Fairgrounds- Gate #7 Aston Ave.
......Small animals - Animal Control mobile trailer (no carrier required)

Hello (School or Windsor Unified School District) Families and Staff Members,

This is a reminder that all WUSD schools are OPEN tomorrow (10-24). PG & E states that Windsor schools are not expected to be impacted by the current Public Safety Power Shutoff event in Sonoma County. We will let you know as soon as reasonably possible if this information changes. Thank you for your patience.

Hola Familias y Empleados del Distrito Escolar de Windsor,

Este es un recordatorio de que todas las escuelas del Distrito de Windsor estarán abiertas mañana (24 de octubre). PG&E nos ha avisado que el apagón de luz para la seguridad pública NO afectará nuestras escuelas. Les avisaremos en cuanto sea posible si hay algún cambio. Gracias por su paciencia.

post_text:
Hello (School or Windsor Unified School District) Families and Staff Members,

This is an important message to let you know that PG & E is advising us of a Public Safety Power Shutoff (PSPS) event in Sonoma County, beginning on October 23 in the late afternoon and through October 24. At this time, all Windsor schools and departments are listed as not being impacted, therefore they will have power and will remain OPEN. We will let you know as soon as reasonably possible if we receive information indicating any changes. Thank you for your patience.

Hola Familias y Empleados del Distrito Escolar de Windsor,

Este es un aviso importante acerca de una notificación de parte de PG&E de que habrá un posible Apagón de luz para la Seguridad Pública en el condado de Sonoma, empezando el 23 de Octubre por la tarde hasta el 24 de Octubre. En este momento y de acuerdo al aviso oficial, todas las escuelas de Windsor y los departamentos del distrito seguirán con luz y se mantendrán abiertos. Les mantendremos informados en cuanto sea posible si hay cualquier cambio. Gracias por su paciencia.
